    <note>Yan(3) Cai [2065] He was a member of a prominent Suzhou lineage. His ancestor Gaoqing's [4092] elder brother, Zhenqing [4086], was Libu shangshu in 779, Taizi taishi in 782, sent on a mission in 783 and died in 785. Gaoqing's son, Hao [4090], was appointed Changshu county magistrate and this marked the beginning of the Suzhou Yan(3). Du [4103] (see below) was the 53rd generation descendant of Luguo Yan(3)zi. The Wuxian branch included the following degree-holders: Cai's father, Changmin [4084], a 1079 jinshi, Cai himself, a 1115 jinshi; his brothers Fu(a) [4088] and Wei [4105], who both earned the degree in 1112, and Wei's grandson, Yan [4110], who earned the juren in 1189, 1201 and finally the jinshi in 1214. The Kunshan xian branch, which moved from Wuxian, begins with Anshi [4083] and his nephew Tianxuan [4101], who received the highest degree in 1118; Tianxuan's nephew, Tang [4100], received the jinshi in 1138, Tang's younger brother, Fa [4087], in 1151, and Tang's cousin, Du, in 1157. Du's younger brother, Zong [4102], was awarded a facilitated degree in 1190. Du's son or nephew, Shuyu [4098], earned the juren in 1186. His other sons and nephews Shuyuan [4099], Shujie [4094], Shuping [4096], and Shuyao [4097] respectively earned the jinshi in 1187, 1190, 1190, 1199, and Shukai [4095] earned the equivalent 1203. Shuyao's nephew, Ying [4111], earned his jinshi in 1226. In addition, the Suzhou Yan(3) who cannot be positively identified with either branch of the lineage include jinshi, Fu(b) [4089], in 1211, juren, Mengying [4093], in 1213, Zikui [4104] and Rongsou [4091], in 1222, X-long [4106] in 1246, Yao [4107] and Yaolin [4109], in 1258, and jinshi, Yaohuan [4108], in 1271 and Zhili [4085], in 1274. The documentation for the Wuxian Yan(3) is Jiangsu jin, 11.8b, 9a; Suzhou FZ, 77.22b; Wujun zhi, 27.1a, 28.7b; YLDD, 2368.4b, 5a, 8b. The documentation for the Kunshan Yan(3) is Jiangsu jin, 11.8b, XTS, 192.1a ff.; Suzhou FZ, 91.9a-9b; ZZTJ, 225.7263, 227.7334, 228.7339, 231.7450; Wujun zhi, 28.9a, 12b, 15a; YLDD, 2368.5a, 5b, 6a, 6b, 7b, 8a, 8b, 9a; Yufeng zhi, 'zhong, 54b. The other Suzhou Yan(3) are documented in Jiangsu jin, 11.10a, 10b, 12a, 12b; YLDD, 2368.8b, 10b. Yan(3) Cai's documentation is Guangdong TZ, 15.12a; YLDD, 2368.5a. CBD, 5, 4209.</note>
